<h2>Charlotte Jones</h2>
<h3>Executive Producer BBC Earth Productions<br />BBC Worldwide</h3>
<div style="float: left;">
  <img src="/CES/media/2014/Conference/SpeakerHeadshots/Charlotte-Jones_11-22-2016-11-00-24-AM.jpg?ext=.jpg" style="margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; max-width: 275px;" alt="Charlotte Jones">
</div>
<div style="margin: 10px;">
  <p>Charlotte joined BBC Earth Productions in May 2012 bringing a wealth of experience to support the rapid expansion into multi-platform production. Working closely with the BBC Worldwide Brands team, this evolution is taking the Earth brand, in its many forms, ever closer to the consumer. Charlotte oversees production in long form programming, digital, short form, virtual reality and content for live events, all made primarily for BBC branded platforms.<br /> <br /> Charlotte's TV experience is as broad as the platforms for which Earth Productions produces. She started her career at UK broadcaster, Channel 4 in the On-air department which led to many channel launches and design projects during the satellite TV boom of the 90s. As a creative director she has worked for channels as diverse as the Discovery Channel, TLC, Bravo, the Parliamentary Channel and MTV. Working both strategically and creatively she has worked on channel design, set design, developing broadcast and scheduling solutions as well as a wide range of content creation from commercials to long form.</p>
<p>After 15 years in&nbsp;broadcast television, Charlotte started producing/directing a wide range of wildlife programming including Nick Baker's Beautiful Freaks, one of the first 3D wildlife documentary to be produced.<br /> <br />Her extensive experience and ability to work across genres and formats has enabled Charlotte to manage Earth Production's dynamic slate. In her first year she exec'd the innovative and creatively challenging ORBI visitor attraction in Yokohama, Japan, launched Earth Unplugged, the BBC's first originated YouTube channel and took the Earth brand via short form onto BBC World News as well as exec&rsquo;ing a broad range of international TV content.</p>
<p>Current projects include 6k originated films for the main theatre at ORBI, content development and creation for Holland America Liners, and the development and production of virtual reality experiences for Oculus and other leading VR platforms.</p>
